# Colocated component structure

Every feature UI lives in a **TitleCase** folder. Match the folder name to the
component (`LoginForm/`, `AdminCommunities/`, `CommunityHome/`).

## Required layout

```
<Name>/
  index.tsx       # UI only — JSX, layout, wiring to the hook
  use<Name>.ts    # Orchestration — forms, toasts, routing, hook composition
  constants.ts    # All user-facing copy (labels, headings, descriptions, CTAs)
  utils.ts        # Pure helpers scoped to this feature (optional)
  types.ts        # Feature-local types (optional)
```

Examples: `LoginForm/useLoginForm.ts`, `Profile/useProfile.ts`,
`AdminCommunities/useAdminCommunities.ts`.

## Hard rules

- **TitleCase folder names only** — never `login-form/`, `admin-communities/`.
- **No kebab-case or snake_case files** inside the folder — use `constants.ts`,
  `utils.ts`, `types.ts`, `use<Name>.ts`, `index.tsx` only.
- **No nested `hooks/`** (or `lib/`, `helpers/`) inside a component folder.
  Domain hooks live in `src/hooks/queries/` and `src/hooks/mutations/`; feature
  orchestration lives in `use<Name>.ts` beside `index.tsx`.
- **`index.tsx` is UI only** — no `fetch`, no Supabase client, no
  `edgeFunctionFetch`, no TanStack `useMutation`/`useQuery` setup, no Zod
  schemas, no toast/modal side effects. Import a colocated `use<Name>` hook and
  render.
- **All user-facing strings in `constants.ts`** — headings, button labels, link
  text, empty states, error titles/descriptions used by this feature. Import
  constants in both `index.tsx` and `use<Name>.ts`. Exception: shared copy used
  across routes belongs in `components/shared/` with its own constants if needed.

## `page.tsx` vs component folder

- `page.tsx` — thin Server Component: prefetch + `<Feature />`. No fat JSX.
- Fat JSX and client logic belong in `components/<Name>/`, not on the page.

## Shared components (`src/components/`)

Same split when a shared component has non-trivial logic:

- `components/shared/<Name>/index.tsx` + `use<Name>.ts` + `constants.ts` as needed.
- `components/ui/` — shadcn primitives; do not add business hooks there.

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — logic + copy inline in index.tsx
export function AdminCommunities() {
  const form = useForm(...);
  async function onSubmit() { await createCommunity(...); }
  return <h1>Communities</h1>;
}

// ✅ GOOD
// constants.ts
export const ADMIN_COMMUNITIES_COPY = {
  title: "Communities",
  createButton: "Create Community",
} as const;

// useAdminCommunities.ts — form, mutations, toasts, navigation
// index.tsx — imports copy + hook; JSX only
```

When editing an existing component that violates this layout, refactor toward
the target structure in the same change when touching that feature.
